[SN]TITLE[SN]
Who should be the next England manager?

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
It was announced on Tuesday that England manager Sam Allardyce had left the job after just 67 days in charge.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
29 September 2016 Last updated at 06:39 BST
It was after claims from a newspaper that he had offered advice on how to get around FA rules on player transfers.
Sam only managed England for one match in 67 days, making him the shortest serving full-time England manager in history.
This means that the Football Association will have to look for another manager for the national side.
We met up with some kids from Bolton to see what they thought England needed to do to improve and who should be the next manager.
